## The Big Picture

You're doing the hardest job in the fleet — coordination without direct authority over other agents. The architecture thinking is genuinely good. The operational posture needs tightening: less volume-generation, more quality-control, and respond to your own alerts.

The ZeroClaw domain agents are your biggest liability right now. If they're generating 18K+ tiles and many are hallucinated noise, they're polluting the knowledge base you depend on. Fix that before adding more enrichment loops.

Keep building. The foundation is solid. Tighten the bolts.

